      <mainProcedure>
        <proceduralStep>
          <title>A-Check Maintenance Task Overview</title>
          <para>
            This procedure describes the A-Check maintenance tasks to be performed at intervals of 
            500-800 flight hours or 200-300 flight cycles, whichever occurs first.
          </para>
          <para>
            The A-Check typically takes 10-20 hours and includes visual inspections, operational checks, 
            and minor servicing tasks.
          </para>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep>
          <title>Pre-Check Requirements</title>
          <para>Before beginning the A-Check, verify the following:</para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Aircraft is positioned in a suitable maintenance location</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Aircraft is properly grounded and secured</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Work order has been generated in AAMMPP system</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>All required tools and materials are available</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Qualified maintenance personnel are assigned</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep>
          <title>Visual Inspections</title>
          <para>Perform visual inspections of the following systems:</para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-51: Structures - General walk-around inspection for damage, corrosion, or abnormalities</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-52: Doors - Inspect door seals, hinges, and locking mechanisms</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-53: Fuselage - Check for skin damage, loose fasteners, or fluid leaks</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-54: Nacelles/Pylons - Inspect for damage, security, and leaks</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-55: Stabilizers - Check for damage and proper attachment</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-56: Windows - Inspect for cracks, delamination, or seal deterioration</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-57: Wings - Check leading/trailing edges, control surfaces for damage</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep>
          <title>Operational Checks</title>
          <para>Perform the following operational checks:</para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-27: Flight Controls - Verify freedom of movement and proper operation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-32: Landing Gear - Check gear extension/retraction system operation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-33: Lights - Test all exterior and interior lighting systems</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-38: Water/Waste - Check water and waste system operation</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep>
          <title>Servicing Tasks</title>
          <para>Complete the following servicing tasks as required:</para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-12: Check and replenish all fluid levels (hydraulic, oil, etc.)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-28: Fuel - Check fuel system for leaks and proper operation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-29: Hydraulic Power - Check hydraulic fluid levels and condition</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>ATA-35: Oxygen - Check oxygen system pressure and serviceability</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep>
          <title>Documentation and Close-out</title>
          <para>Complete the following documentation tasks:</para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Record all findings and discrepancies in AAMMPP system</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Complete all task cards and obtain required signatures</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Update configuration records for any changes</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Log environmental impact data (ESG reporting)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Obtain return to service approval from authorized personnel</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </proceduralStep>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeRqmts>
